#The continue statement in Python returns the control to the beginning of the while loop.
#The continue statement rejects all the remaining statements in the current iteration of the loop and moves
#the control back to the top of the loop.The continue statement can be used in both while and for loops.
var = 10                    
while var > 0:              
   var = var -1
   if var == 5:
      continue
   print('Current variable value :', var)
